  <exercise xml:id="I1-16-f">
    <title>Compare to actual 1932 results</title>
    <statement>
      <p>Now find the <url href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1932_United_States_presidential_election">actual 1932 election results</url>, what proportion of voters voted for the Republican (Hoover) candidate (among the three major candidates)? Did the Literary Digest poll have too many or too few Republican voters? How could we account for this in our estimates of vote count?</p>
    </statement>
    <response>
    </response>
    <solution>
      <p>15,761,254/(15,761,254 + 22,821,277 + 73,158) = 0.399</p>
      <p>The proportion who claimed to vote Republican in the survey (0.507) is noticeably larger than the proportion that actually voted Republican (0.399). This supports the suspicion that the survey overrepresented Republicans compared to the voting population.</p>
    </solution>
